springVersion = "I am honored that you would lend me your genuine consideration, especially in such a turbulent time. If you accept my proposal, I can assure you that I will be well worth your while. Oh, but there will be more time for flirting later!—right now, there are matters of life and death to discuss.

I have heard rumors of various plots growing in the South. On this, I can’t say much. As we are not formally allied (yet), my allegiance is foremost to my kingdom. Besides, some secrets are too dangerous to barter with in something as flimsy as paper and ink. I will only advise you to…reassess your late father’s policies, and make your stance clear to the Majani Assembly as soon as possible. 

The Savanna Avians are not like us Northerners. I may deal in secrets, but they have always been wary of those with uncertain motives. There are debts to be paid, Your Majesty. If not in coin, then honor. Eventually, someone will be sent to collect. Be careful."
